						<summary>

						<p>Chōḻa, Rājarāja Rājakēsarivarman Rājarāja I, 26th year = A.D. 1011.</p>						

						<p>Gift of money for a lamp by a local merchant called Karuvūr Chūṟṟi, to the temple of Tirumēṟṟaḷi-Mahādēva at Tiruvēṅgaivāyil, a <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna</hi> in Peruvāyi-nāḍu, a sub-division of Pāṇdikulāśani-vaḷanāḍu.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">IPS</hi>, No. 88.]</p>						

